t female sexuality continue to influence the practice of law and medicine today.This book offers new insights and provides a wealth of up-to- date information on a subject that changes every day. The text is divided into three main parts: political issues of pre- conception, the politics of pregnancy, and the politics of motherhood. Throughout, Meyer argues passionately that while technology and medicine must progress, they should not be allowed to do so at women's expense.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aBirth controlxPolitical aspects. 0aHuman reproductionxPolitical aspects. 0aHuman reproductionxSocial aspects. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxPolitical aspects. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxSocial aspects. 0aSex discrimination against women. 0aWomen's rights. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814763209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814763209.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK